1. Create Demand for Currency

People must obtain dollars to pay taxes.

This guarantees demand for the currency.

2. Remove Money From Circulation

Taxes effectively destroy money in the monetary system.

When taxes are paid:

bank deposits decrease

government balances increase

money supply contracts

3. Control Inflation

Taxes reduce excess purchasing power.

They help stabilize prices.

4. Government Spending Actually Creates Money

When the government spends, it injects money into the economy.

